1 (a) "Underinsured motor vehicle" means a land motor vehicle for which the ownership,
2 maintenance, or use is insured or bonded for bodily injury liability at the time of the accident, but the limits of the
3 liability are less than the total damages that the injured person is legally entitled to recover.
4 (b) "Uninsured motor vehicle" means a land motor vehicle for which the ownership, maintenance,
5 or use is not insured or bonded for bodily injury liability at the time of the accident."
